				<h2>Class structure and UML diagram</h2>
				<h3>Classes:</h3>
				<br/>
				<ol>
					<li>
						<b>Card:</b>
						A base class that represents a playing card with suit and value properties. It provides methods to retrieve these attributes.
					</li>
					<br/>
					<li>
						<b>CardGraphic:</b>
						This class is a extention of Card class and adds a getGraphic() method that returns a Unicode symbol for each card.
					</li>
					<br/>
					<li>
						<b>Deck:</b>
						This class containes a collection of Card objects. This class has the method to create, shuffle and draw card from the collection of cards in the game that is a total of 52 at the start excluding the jockers.
					</li>
					<br/>
				</ol>
				<h3>Relationships between classes:</h3>
				<br/>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<b>Inheritance:</b>
						The CardGraphic-class inherits from the Card-class using the 'extends' keyword in php.
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>Composition:</b>
						The Deck-class has many Card-objects.
					</li>
				</ul>
